name: appmixer.ai.bedrock.Converse
author: Appmixer <info@appmixer.com>
description: Send messages to an LLM and receive a response. Apart from sending text prompts, Converse also supports video, audio, documents and image prompts.

fileId.label: File
fileId.tooltip: You can pass a file as an input to your model. This can only be used for files up to 2MB in size.

s3ObjectBucket.label: S3 Object Bucket
s3ObjectBucket.tooltip: You can pass an S3 object as an input to your model. Select a bucket where your S3 object is located.

s3ObjectKey.label: S3 Object Key
s3ObjectKey.tooltip: You can pass an S3 object as an input to your model. Enter an object key to use as input to your model.

customInput.label: Custom Model Input

key.label: Key
key.tooltip: The key of the input parameter.

value.label: Value
value.tooltip: The value of the input parameter.

type.label: Type
type.tooltip: The type of the input parameter.

customInput.tooltip: Different models require different input parameter formats. Please refer to the model documentation for the correct input format. For example, the Anthropic Claud text models expect prompt (required), temperature, ....; while the Amazon Titan text models expect inputText as a required parameter. Use the Custom Model Input to define a custom input if your model does not support the standard input format which. In this case, leave the Messages field empty. Also, you can use the Custom Model Input to add any additional parameters next to the standard input format, for example temperature or max_tokens.

region.label: Region
region.tooltip: Your AWS instance region. If not select, us-east-1 will be used as default.

model.label: Model
model.tooltip: ID of the model to use.
